A '''distortion meter''' is a type of [[electronic test equipment]] used to determine specific [[frequencies]] that cause distortion in electronic devices. The device is primarily used in [[Audio equipment|audio related equipment]].
==Features and uses== A typical unit injects a [[Signal (electronics)|signal]] in to the input of a circuit and monitors the output of the circuit for distortion.
